 | A-077 | The optional `approval_actions.digital_signature_id` is stored as a nullable UUID reference until the source §16.6 `signature_records` owner is implemented; 007C/007D must not treat an arbitrary UUID as verified signature evidence. | Data-model §15.4 names a foreign key, but the repository has no `SignatureRecord` model yet and creating the documentation/signature aggregate in approval routing would cross the selected slice boundary. Retaining the nullable identifier preserves the source column without inventing a signature target. | `docs/source/data-model.md` §15.4 and §16.6; `docs/slices/007C-cfo-and-director-threshold-routing.md` | 007C, 007D, and the signature-record owning documentation slice | Medium | Yes | 2026-07-13 | Replace the UUID field with a protected nullable FK when `signature_records` lands; reject non-null action signature ids until then. |
 | A-078 | A permissioned member-list caller with no persisted member scope receives the source-required filtered `200` empty page rather than a collection-level `403`; detail and mutations retain `403 OBJECT_ACCESS_DENIED`. Actorless active-member calculation is authorized only by its owning application or authenticated portal account, not by a direct member calculation scope. | 006Z15's blanket no-scope/assigned wording conflicts with auth §32.1 queryset filtering and with its own requirements 5-6, which require owning-object derivation and forbid restoring a direct actor calculation interface. The source-compliant public behavior is therefore empty collection nondisclosure plus application/portal ownership. | `docs/source/auth-permissions.md` §§24.1, 25.1, 32.1, 34.2; `docs/source/codebase-design.md` §§26.1-26.3; `docs/slices/006Z15-member-public-action-authority-matrix-closure.md` requirements 2-6; A-072 | 006Z15-member-public-action-authority-matrix-closure | High | No | 2026-07-13 | Matrix evidence executes list, detail, mutation, application, portal, and borrower-limit interfaces separately; no permission, role, or member-scope fact is presented as authority for the actorless calculation. |
