+| A-079 | A 007D sanction decision copies the frozen appraisal's recommended amount, tenure, interest-rate type, and security summary. Numeric interest/penal rates and repayment date remain null, charges remain `{}`, and conditions precedent remain blank until an approved source-owned rate/repayment/condition snapshot exists. Return-for-clarification restores the source-defined `appraisal_reviewed` pre-committee application and appraisal state. | API §25.8 requires these decision fields, but the current reviewed appraisal stores no numeric rate, repayment date, charges, penal rate, or conditions-precedent facts. Calculating or inventing them at approval time would create financial/business rules absent from the source. | `docs/source/api-contracts.md` §25.8; `docs/source/data-model.md` §8.1/§15.5; `docs/source/functional-spec.md` M05-FR-007/008; `docs/source/auth-permissions.md` §20.1 | 007D and later rate/documentation owners | High | Yes | 2026-07-13 | Later owners may populate these fields only from versioned approved source facts; historical sanction decisions remain immutable. |
